# Employee portal — mobile-first

Design and implement **mobile first**, then enhance at `sm` / `md` / `lg`.

## Layout

- Use full-width blocks by default; constrain width only from `sm:` or `md:` upward.
- Prefer `flex-col` / `grid-cols-1` on base; switch to row/multi-column at breakpoints.
- Avoid large fixed `min-h` on cards for mobile; use `min-h-0` or content-driven height.
- Truncate long names/IDs (`min-w-0`, `truncate`) so headers do not overflow.

## Touch & actions

- Primary actions: **min ~44px height** on mobile (`min-h-11` / `h-11`), may shrink on `sm:` (`sm:min-h-9`).
- Header actions: two-column grid on mobile (`epHeaderActions` from `@/lib/employee-portal-ui`).
- Full-width buttons on mobile; `sm:w-auto` on desktop.

## Dialogs

- Use `epDialogContent` or `epDialogContentWide` — near full viewport width, `max-h` + `overflow-y-auto` on small screens.
- Form footer buttons: stack full-width on mobile (`epFormActions`, `epFormActionButton`).

## Typography

- Page titles: `PageTitle` (`text-xl` → `md:text-2xl`), not `H1`.
- Subtext/descriptions: `PageSubtitle` or `BodySmall` + `text-muted-foreground` — **sentence case**, end with a period. Do not title-case every word.
- Form labels: `BodySmall` or `Label`, not mono uppercase `Caption` for field labels.

## Motion

- Skip hover translate/lift on touch: `motion-safe:md:hover:…` or `epCardInteractive`.

## Reuse

Import shared classes from `@/lib/employee-portal-ui` instead of duplicating mobile/desktop class strings.

- Page root: `epPageWrapper` only — never `VStack gap` + `epPageStack` together (doubles vertical spacing on phones).
- Form cards: `epFormCard` on request/form `Card` roots (clips iOS date/time overflow).
- Native `<select>`: `epNativeSelect` (44px touch height, `min-w-0`).
- Split layouts: `EpMobileBlock` / `EpDesktopBlock` when mobile and desktop need different markup (see header in `EmployeePortalHeader.tsx`).
- Layout uses `env(safe-area-inset-*)` for iOS home indicator and notches; test on tall phones (e.g. iPhone 16 Pro Max, Pixel 8 Pro).
